msgctxt "112_Taichi"
msgid "Taichi in the house!"
msgstr "Taichi in the house!"

msgctxt "124_Koji"
msgid "Yo!"
msgstr "¡Hey!"

msgctxt "148_Ayako"
msgid "We're home, Uncle Kaz!"
msgstr "We're home, Uncle Kaz!"

msgctxt "160_Kiryu"
msgid "Looks like you kids had a good trip."
msgstr "Looks like you kids had a good trip."

msgctxt "172_Kiryu"
msgid "You enjoy yourselves?"
msgstr "You enjoy yourselves?"

msgctxt "184_Taichi"
msgid "Oh yeah, it was awesome! We hiked, went camping, even saw some old bones and stuff at a museum!"
msgstr "Oh yeah, it was awesome! We hiked, went camping, even saw some old bones and stuff at a museum!"

msgctxt "196_Taichi"
msgid "Wasn't it super cool, Koji?"
msgstr "Wasn't it super cool, Koji?"

msgctxt "208_Koji"
msgid "Mhm! You gotta go with us sometime, Uncle Kaz!"
msgstr "Mhm! You gotta go with us sometime, Uncle Kaz!"

msgctxt "220_Koji"
msgid "How was your grade's trip, Ayako?"
msgstr "How was your grade's trip, Ayako?"

msgctxt "232_Ayako"
msgid "Great!"
msgstr "¡Genial!"

msgctxt "256_Hamazaki"
msgid "A year back, when I was still suckling the Tojo Clan teat,\\r\n"
"I found out that the top brass over at the Tokyo PD had\\r\n"
"their hands dirty... real dirty, with tons of shady cash."
msgstr "A year back, when I was still suckling the Tojo Clan teat,\\r\n"
"I found out that the top brass over at the Tokyo PD had\\r\n"
"their hands dirty... real dirty, with tons of shady cash."

msgctxt "268_Hamazaki"
msgid "Bet you can guess where I learned all that."
msgstr "Bet you can guess where I learned all that."

msgctxt "280_Kiryu"
msgid "The Snake Flower."
msgstr "The Snake Flower."

msgctxt "292_Hamazaki"
msgid "Yup. They'd been working with one of the top men on the\\r\n"
"force for years. Laundered his money through foreign banks\\r\n"
"and everything."
msgstr "Yup. They'd been working with one of the top men on the\\r\n"
"force for years. Laundered his money through foreign banks\\r\n"
"and everything."

msgctxt "304_Kiryu"
msgid "Why go through all that trouble, though? What did the police\\r\n"
"need with all that cash?"
msgstr "Why go through all that trouble, though? What did the police\\r\n"
"need with all that cash?"

msgctxt "316_Hamazaki"
msgid "What they needed... was to build what one of their highest-ranking boys called their \"utopia.\""
msgstr "What they needed... was to build what one of their highest-ranking boys called their \"utopia.\""

msgctxt "328_Kiryu"
msgid "Penitentiary No. 2."
msgstr "Penitentiary No. 2."

msgctxt "340_Hamazaki"
msgid "Right again. The idea was, they'd build a place to toss all\\r\n"
"the convicted yakuza they round up, then go and make deals\\r\n"
"with those very same yakuza."
msgstr "Right again. The idea was, they'd build a place to toss all\\r\n"
"the convicted yakuza they round up, then go and make deals\\r\n"
"with those very same yakuza."

msgctxt "352_Kiryu"
msgid "What kind of deals?"
msgstr "What kind of deals?"

msgctxt "364_Hamazaki"
msgid "Stuff like bribing people to commit crimes. Then when the\\r\n"
"cops came in and saved the day, everyone'd think they were\\r\n"
"the heroes. Crime would become a police-controlled affair."
msgstr "Stuff like bribing people to commit crimes. Then when the\\r\n"
"cops came in and saved the day, everyone'd think they were\\r\n"
"the heroes. Crime would become a police-controlled affair."

msgctxt "376_Kiryu"
msgid "That's absurd."
msgstr "That's absurd."

msgctxt "388_Hamazaki"
msgid "Yeah, an absurd power grab. Whoever handled those \"crimes\"\\r\n"
"would get big brownie points on the force. End up rocketing up the ranks."
msgstr "Yeah, an absurd power grab. Whoever handled those \"crimes\"\\r\n"
"would get big brownie points on the force. End up rocketing up the ranks."

msgctxt "400_Kiryu"
msgid "I still can't believe the ten billion Jingu was trying to\\r\n"
"launder through the Tojo... was supposed to end up with\\r\n"
"the cops."
msgstr "I still can't believe the ten billion Jingu was trying to\\r\n"
"launder through the Tojo... was supposed to end up with\\r\n"
"the cops."

msgctxt "412_Hamazaki"
msgid "Believe me, I was just as surprised as you when I found out."
msgstr "Believe me, I was just as surprised as you when I found out."

msgctxt "424_Hamazaki"
msgid "Even with the money getting blown to high heaven, the paper\\r\n"
"trail alone is some serious shit."
msgstr "Even with the money getting blown to high heaven, the paper\\r\n"
"trail alone is some serious shit."

msgctxt "436_Hamazaki"
msgid "Honestly, the only reason I grabbed this file in the first place is 'cause I wanted a little dirt on the warden. Something I could use to bargain my way outta there, you know."
msgstr "Honestly, the only reason I grabbed this file in the first place is 'cause I wanted a little dirt on the warden. Something I could use to bargain my way outta there, you know."

msgctxt "448_Hamazaki"
msgid "But I gotta say. I never thought I'd stumble on a shitstorm\\r\n"
"this massive."
msgstr "But I gotta say. I never thought I'd stumble on a shitstorm\\r\n"
"this massive."

msgctxt "460_Hamazaki"
msgid "Almost feels like it's outta my league, if you get me."
msgstr "Almost feels like it's outta my league, if you get me."

msgctxt "472_Hamazaki"
msgid "I show up on Tokyo PD's doorstep with this baby in tow and\\r\n"
"that'd be the last anyone ever hears of me."
msgstr "I show up on Tokyo PD's doorstep with this baby in tow and\\r\n"
"that'd be the last anyone ever hears of me."

msgctxt "484_Kiryu"
msgid "Hm..."
msgstr "Mm..."

msgctxt "496_Hamazaki"
msgid "Turns out this file's not the bargaining chip I was hoping\\r\n"
"it'd be. It's yours now."
msgstr "Turns out this file's not the bargaining chip I was hoping\\r\n"
"it'd be. It's yours now."

msgctxt "508_Kiryu"
msgid "But why me?"
msgstr "But why me?"

msgctxt "520_Hamazaki"
msgid "'Cause you were at the center of everything that went down five years ago."
msgstr "'Cause you were at the center of everything that went down five years ago."

msgctxt "532_Hamazaki"
msgid "Hell, you even had to beat the shit outta your own brother\\r\n"
"at the end of it all. Then..."
msgstr "Hell, you even had to beat the shit outta your own brother\\r\n"
"at the end of it all. Then..."

msgctxt "556_Hamazaki"
msgid "Kiryu?"
msgstr "Kiryu?"

msgctxt "568_Kiryu"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "580_Hamazaki"
msgid "C'mon, don't gimme the silent treatment here."
msgstr "C'mon, don't gimme the silent treatment here."

msgctxt "592_Kiryu"
msgid "I just don't get it. Why did you show me that?"
msgstr "I just don't get it. Why did you show me that?"

msgctxt "604_Hamazaki"
msgid "I already told you. You gotta go to Kamurocho and tell\\r\n"
"my boy Saejima what really－"
msgstr "I already told you. You gotta go to Kamurocho and tell\\r\n"
"my boy Saejima what really－"

msgctxt "616_Kiryu"
msgid "There's more to it than that. I know there is. Besides, you\\r\n"
"would end up behind bars again in no time without this \"bargaining chip\" of yours."
msgstr "There's more to it than that. I know there is. Besides, you\\r\n"
"would end up behind bars again in no time without this \"bargaining chip\" of yours."

msgctxt "628_Kiryu"
msgid "So tell me, Hamazaki. What are you really after?"
msgstr "So tell me, Hamazaki. What are you really after?"

msgctxt "652_Kiryu"
msgid "So, Hamazaki. What do you want?"
msgstr "So, Hamazaki. What do you want?"

msgctxt "664_Hamazaki"
msgid "Well, it's kinda a long story, but Saejima..."
msgstr "Well, it's kinda a long story, but Saejima..."

msgctxt "676_Hamazaki"
msgid "He's the guy who bumped off Yoshiharu Ueno, chairman of the\\r\n"
"Ueno Seiwa, back in '85."
msgstr "He's the guy who bumped off Yoshiharu Ueno, chairman of the\\r\n"
"Ueno Seiwa, back in '85."

msgctxt "688_Kiryu"
msgid "Wait, that's..."
msgstr "Wait, that's..."

msgctxt "700_Hamazaki"
msgid "Yup. You spend enough time in Kamurocho, you're gonna hear\\r\n"
"the story."
msgstr "Yup. You spend enough time in Kamurocho, you're gonna hear\\r\n"
"the story."

msgctxt "712_Hamazaki"
msgid "Saejima killed eighteen men all by himself that day."
msgstr "Saejima killed eighteen men all by himself that day."

msgctxt "724_Kiryu"
msgid "That's what they say."
msgstr "That's what they say."

msgctxt "736_Hamazaki"
msgid "Anyways, the two of us only just met. Both locked up in a\\r\n"
"private prison a stone's throw away from here."
msgstr "Anyways, the two of us only just met. Both locked up in a\\r\n"
"private prison a stone's throw away from here."

msgctxt "748_Kiryu"
msgid "What do you mean, \"private\" prison?"
msgstr "What do you mean, \"private\" prison?"

msgctxt "760_Hamazaki"
msgid "I mean, the government's not involved. They put the contract\\r\n"
"in place, yeah, but the private sector's been running the joint since the day they broke ground."
msgstr "I mean, the government's not involved. They put the contract\\r\n"
"in place, yeah, but the private sector's been running the joint since the day they broke ground."

msgctxt "772_Hamazaki"
msgid "They call it Okinawa Penitentiary No. 2. Take it you never\\r\n"
"heard the name?"
msgstr "They call it Okinawa Penitentiary No. 2. Take it you never\\r\n"
"heard the name?"

msgctxt "784_Kiryu"
msgid "No. I had no idea a place like that existed in Okinawa."
msgstr "No. I had no idea a place like that existed in Okinawa."

msgctxt "796_Hamazaki"
msgid "They officially call it a correctional facility, but that's\\r\n"
"a load of bull. It's a dumping ground for washed-up yakuza\\r\n"
"they wanna snuff out for good."
msgstr "Oficialmente le llaman un \"centro correccional,\" pero eso es pura mamada. Es un tiradero para yakuza acabados que quieren deshacerse de una vez por todas."

msgctxt "808_Hamazaki"
msgid "Was only a few days ago that Saejima got shipped down from\\r\n"
"whatever shithole they had him in up in Tokyo."
msgstr "Apenas hace unos días que Saejima fue enviado desde el maldito agujero en el que lo tenían allá en Tokio, güey."

msgctxt "820_Kiryu"
msgid "Which is when you met."
msgstr "Which is when you met."

msgctxt "832_Hamazaki"
msgid "Bingo."
msgstr "Exacto."

msgctxt "844_Kiryu"
msgid "And you two planned the jailbreak together?"
msgstr "And you two planned the jailbreak together?"

msgctxt "856_Hamazaki"
msgid "More or less. Though I'm the one who came up with the idea,\\r\n"
"if I'm being honest."
msgstr "¡Exacto, amigo! No estaba metido desde el principio Saejima\\r\n"
"Necesitaba a alguien para ayudarlo a coordinar la fuga. ¡Ándale!"

msgctxt "868_Kiryu"
msgid "Why'd you pick Saejima as your partner?"
msgstr "Why'd you pick Saejima as your partner?"

msgctxt "880_Hamazaki"
msgid "You saw him, right? Guy's built like a freaking brick wall."
msgstr "¡Lo viste, ¿verdad? Ese vato es fuerte como un muro de ladrillos, compadre."

msgctxt "892_Hamazaki"
msgid "More importantly... I knew what really happened back in '85.\\r\n"
"The truth."
msgstr "Lo más importante... \\r\n"
"yo sabía la verdá de lo que pasó en el '85. La neta."

msgctxt "904_Kiryu"
msgid "Go on."
msgstr "Dime."

msgctxt "916_Hamazaki"
msgid "Back in the day, Saejima was real tight with Majima. Yeah,\\r\n"
"that Majima."
msgstr "¡En aquellos años, compadre, Saejima y Majima eran como pata y uña! ¡Sí, sí, ese mismo Majima! ¡De verdad te lo digo, amigo!"

msgctxt "928_Hamazaki"
msgid "And that Ueno Seiwa hit? The one where Saejima slaughtered\\r\n"
"those eighteen guys? That was originally gonna be a two man\\r\n"
"job. Saejima and Majima."
msgstr "¡Andale! Ese jale del Ueno Seiwa, donde Saejima se despachó a esos dieciocho tipos, ¡originalmente iban a ser dos en el cotorreo! Saejima y Majima, ¡compadre! ¡Qué tal, eh!"

msgctxt "940_Kiryu"
msgid "Majima-san and Saejima were accomplices?"
msgstr "Majima-san and Saejima were accomplices?"

msgctxt "952_Hamazaki"
msgid "Yup. But the day of the attack, Majima never showed. That\\r\n"
"betrayal's how I convinced Saejima to break out with me."
msgstr "¡Exacto! Pero el día del asalto, Majima nunca se presentó. \\r\n"
"Esa traición fue lo que convenció a Saejima de romperla conmigo, ¡vato! ¡Ya ves cómo es la vida, compadre!"

msgctxt "964_Kiryu"
msgid "Explains why Saejima was talking about revenge when he was\\r\n"
"here."
msgstr "Explains why Saejima was talking about revenge when he was\\r\n"
"here."

msgctxt "976_Hamazaki"
msgid "It's all bullshit, though. Majima would never have betrayed\\r\n"
"his brother."
msgstr "¡Eso es pura bazofia, compadre! Majima jamás hubiera traicionado a su hermano."

msgctxt "988_Hamazaki"
msgid "They were both set up."
msgstr "Ambos fueron chamaqueados, compa."

msgctxt "1000_Kiryu"
msgid "By who?"
msgstr "By who?"

msgctxt "1012_Hamazaki"
msgid "Guy named Shibata. Was heading up a third-tier Tojo family\\r\n"
"at the time."
msgstr "Un tal Shibata. Estaba liderando un gumi de tercera en el Tojo-kai en ese entonces, compadre."

msgctxt "1024_Hamazaki"
msgid "Problem is, Saejima and I got split up before I got to tell\\r\n"
"him what really happened."
msgstr "El pedo es que nos separaron antes de que le pudiera contar toda la neta a Saejima, compadre."

msgctxt "1036_Kiryu"
msgid "I think I can guess the favor you want."
msgstr "I think I can guess the favor you want."

msgctxt "1048_Hamazaki"
msgid "Yeah. You gotta tell him the truth, no matter what."
msgstr "¡Claro que sí, amigo! Tienes que decírsela, no importa ni madres. ¡Es la pura y santa verdad, compadre!"

msgctxt "1060_Kiryu"
msgid "Why is it so important?"
msgstr "Why is it so important?"

msgctxt "1072_Hamazaki"
msgid "As it stands, Saejima's gonna try and kill Majima. Not only\\r\n"
"that, but..."
msgstr "No solo eso, amigo, sino que Saejima va a ir a matar a Majima. Y además... ¡le va a romper toda su madre!"

msgctxt "1084_Kiryu"
msgid "But?"
msgstr "¿Pero?"

msgctxt "1096_Hamazaki"
msgid "But... I really respect him. He doesn't deserve to be living life in the dark, you know?"
msgstr "¡Peroóó!... Le tengo un respeto de la gran fregada, ¿sabes? No merece estar viviendo en la oscuridad, amigo. ¡Es tiempo de que conozca la verdad!"

msgctxt "1108_Kiryu"
msgid "Hm."
msgstr "Hm."

msgctxt "1120_Hamazaki"
msgid "I mean, sure, I only asked him to help me bust out 'cause\\r\n"
"of how tough he is."
msgstr "Es cierto, sólo le pedí que me ayudara a salir porque es un maldito roble. Pero ahora... ¡necesita saber toda la historia, wey! ¡No puede seguir cargando con esa bronca!"

msgctxt "1132_Hamazaki"
msgid "But he actually started trusting me during the escape. Me,\\r\n"
"of all people!"
msgstr "¡Pero luego durante la fuga, el carnalito comenzó a confiar en mí! ¡En mí, de todos los güeyes!"

msgctxt "1144_Kiryu"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "1156_Hamazaki"
msgid "Look. My life's been nothing but betrayal after betrayal.\\r\n"
"I've been on both sides of that coin."
msgstr "¡Mira, compadre! ¡Mi vida ha sido pura y purita traición tras traición! ¡He estado en ambos laditos de esa monedita! ¡Ajúa!"

msgctxt "1168_Hamazaki"
msgid "But two people looked beyond all that. Chose to trust me\\r\n"
"anyway. You... and Saejima."
msgstr "¡Ay, chico! ¡Pero dos personas miraron más allá de todo eso! Decidieron confiar en mí de todas formas. Tú... y Saejima. ¡Ándale!"

msgctxt "1180_Kiryu"
msgid "Hamazaki..."
msgstr "Hamazaki..."

msgctxt "1192_Hamazaki"
msgid "I want another chance. To start over, be a true brother to\\r\n"
"a guy who went out on a limb and actually trusted me."
msgstr "¡Orale! Quiero otra oportunidad. Empezar de nuevo y ser un verdadero hermano para un vato que se arriesgó y de verdad confió en mí. ¡Ándele!"

msgctxt "1204_Hamazaki"
msgid "So I'm begging you, Kiryu-san. You gotta help me!"
msgstr "¡Por favor, Kiryu-san! ¡Necesito que me eches una mano, compadre!"

msgctxt "1228_Kiryu"
msgid "One question first."
msgstr "Una pregunta primero."

msgctxt "1240_Hamazaki"
msgid "What's that?"
msgstr "¿Purgatorio?"

msgctxt "1252_Kiryu"
msgid "Why do you need me to do it? Can't you go tell Saejima all\\r\n"
"this yourself?"
msgstr "Why do you need me to do it? Can't you go tell Saejima all\\r\n"
"this yourself?"

msgctxt "1264_Hamazaki"
msgid "Well, I..."
msgstr "Bueno, yo..."

msgctxt "1276_Kiryu"
msgid "What is it, Hamazaki?"
msgstr "What is it, Hamazaki?"

